header: Test vectors of type Keywrap are intended for tests
checking the wrapping and unwrapping of key material.

CounterOverflow.description: The test vector contains a value that is long enough so that the round counter overflows at 256.

ModifiedPadding.description: The test vector contains a ciphertext that was obtained with a modified padding. Unwrapping should verify the padding and hence reject this test vector.

Normal.description: The test vector contains a pseudorandomly generated, valid test case. Implementations are expected to pass this test.

SmallKey.description: This test vector wraps a key smaller than 128-bits. Rejecting such keys may be reasonable to detect weak keys. Rejecting the keys also simplifies the implementation.
